rimination. She offers changes for determining Indigenous identity and citizenship and argues that First Nations must determine citizenship themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIndians of North AmericaxLegal status, laws, etc.zCanada. 0aIndians of North AmericaxTribal citizenshipzCanada. 7aLAW / Indigenous Peoples.2bisacsh1 aDay, Isadore, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontour, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaul, Candice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaul, Lawrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978189583073640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781895830736423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781895830736/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles